        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Genesis 40</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="line-8-2" n="8" prev="ADub.III.73.001.039.trl.xml#line-8-1" />
                        <l n="1">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            And it was after these things, the cup-bearer
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            of the king of Egypt and his baker sinned against
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            their lord the king of Egypt.</l>
                        <l n="2">And Pharaoh
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            was angry at his two officers, at the superior of the cup-bearers,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            and at the superior of the bakers.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                        <l n="3">And he put them under the guard of the house of the superior
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            of the executioners, into prison, the place where Joseph
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            was imprisoned.</l>
                        <l n="4">And the superior
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            of the executioners assigned Joseph with them, and he served
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            them. <seg type="commented" n="#seg001" />And they were one year under
                                guard.<anchor type="commented" xml:id="seg001" /><ref target="#fn1"
                                type="noteAnchor" /></l>
                        <l n="5">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            the two of them dreamed a dream, each his dream, in one night, each man
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            according to the interpretation of his dream, the cup-bearer and the baker
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            of the king of Egypt, who were imprisoned
                            <milestone unit="page" n="66r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            in the prison.</l>
                        <l n="6">And Joseph came in to them in the morning, and saw
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            them, and, lo, they turned pale.</l>
                        <l n="7">And he asked
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            <addSpan spanTo="#add001" /><emph>Pharaoh’s</emph><anchor
                                xml:id="add001" /> officers that were with him under guard in his
                            lord’s house, saying,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            ‘Why do your faces look so bad today?’</l>
                        <l n="8">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            they said to him, ‘We have dreamed a dream, and there is no interpreter
                            of it.’
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            And Joseph said to them, ‘Lo, interpretations are in the hand of God.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            Now, tell me them.’</l>
                        <l n="9">And the superior
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            cup-bearer told his dream to Joseph, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            said to him, ‘In my dream, lo, a vine was before me,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="10">And in the vine were three branches. As soon as it budded,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            its blossoms shot forth, and its bunches ripened into grapes.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="11">And Pharaoh’s cup was in my hand. And I took the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            grapes, and pressed them into Pharaoh’s cup, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            I gave the cup into Pharaoh’s hand.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                        <l n="12">And Joseph said to him, ‘This is the interpretation of it: The three
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            branches are three days.</l>
                        <l n="13">Yet within three days
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            Pharaoh shall lift up your head, and restore you to your place,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            and you shall give Pharaoh’s cup to his hand, after the former
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            manner of life when you were his cup-bearer.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="14">But only remember me <addSpan spanTo="#add002" /><emph>with
                                you</emph><anchor xml:id="add002" /> when it shall be good for you, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            practice kindness with me, and make mention of me to Pharaoh,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="66v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            and bring me out of this house.</l>
                        <l n="15">Because I was stolen
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            away out of the land of the Hebrews, and also here I have done
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            nothing that they should put me into the prison.’</l>
                        <l n="16">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            the superior of the bakers saw that the interpretation was good, and he
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            said to Joseph, ‘Me too. In my dream: and, lo, I had three white
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            bread baskets on my head.</l>
                        <l n="17">And in the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            highest basket were |some| of all of Pharaoh’s foods, the work of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            bakers, but the birds ate them out of the basket on my head.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="18">And Joseph answered and said, ‘This
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            is the interpretation thereof: The three baskets are three days.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                        <l n="19">Yet within three days Pharaoh shall lift your head up from you,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            and shall hang you on a tree. And the birds shall eat
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            your flesh from you.’</l>
                        <l n="20">And it was
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            on the third day, it was Pharaoh’s birthday, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            he made a feast for all his servants. And he lifted up the head of the superior
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            of the cup-bearers and of the superior baker
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            among his servants.</l>
                        <l n="21">And he
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            restored the superior of the cup-bearers to his position
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            of cup-bearership, and he gave the cup
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            in Pharaoh’s hand.</l>
                        <l n="22">But he hanged the superior of the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            bakers, as Joseph had interpreted to them.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="67r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="23">And the chief cupbearer did not remember
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            Joseph. And he forgot him.</l>
                    </ab>
